notes: The National Certificates of Educational Achievement (NCEA) are New Zealand's main secondary school qualifications. NCEA level 2 is usually studied in year 12 of schooling. The NCEA level 2 attainment rate is the percentage of participating students who achieve level 2.

Better Public Services' Result 5 is to increase the proportion of 18-year-olds with NCEA Level 2 or equivalent qualification. The target is 85% of 18-year-olds will have achieved NCEA Level 2 or an equivalent qualification in 2017.
MELAA refers to Middle-Eastern, Latin American or African ethnicity. These are annual figures.
A percentage point (pp) is the unit for the arithmetic difference of two percentages.
